snippet: The victory, after an abbreviated and contentious contest with some of the state’s best-known Democrats, makes Mr. Booker a heavy favorite to win the October general election.
abstract: Newark Mayor Cory A Booker easily wins Democratic nomination for United States Senate, and is heavy favorite to win October general election in an overwhelmingly Democratic state that has not elected a Republican senator in four decades; if Booker does win, he will become nation's only elected black senator; Steven M Lonegan wins Republican primary.
lead_paragraph: The victory, after an abbreviated and contentious contest with some of the state’s best-known Democrats, makes Mr. Booker a heavy favorite to win the October general election.

headline.main: Booker Coasts in Primary; ‘Make Me Your Senator,’ He Tells New Jersey
